Now I explain your full flow in very simple beginner way step-by-step.

Repository is on GitHub

We have:

master branch → main code

rahul2 branch → your working branch
____________________________________________________________________________________
🎯 Your Goal

👉 Take latest code from master
👉 Put it into rahul2
👉 Fix conflict if it happens
👉 Push everything to GitHub
____________________________________________________________________________________
✅ Step-By-Step Simple Explanation
1️⃣ git checkout master

👉 Switch to master branch.

Meaning:

“Go to main branch.”
____________________________________________________________________________________
2️⃣ git pull

👉 Download latest code from GitHub.

Meaning:

“Update my master branch with latest online version.”

Now master is updated.
____________________________________________________________________________________
3️⃣ git checkout rahul2

👉 Switch to your working branch.

Now you are inside rahul2.
____________________________________________________________________________________
4️⃣ git merge master

👉 Bring master changes into rahul2.

Meaning:

“Update my rahul2 branch with latest master code.”

🔥 If Conflict Happens

Git will show:

CONFLICT (content)

Don’t panic 😄
____________________________________________________________________________________
🛠 How To Fix Conflict (Very Simple)
1️⃣ Open file (example: abc)

Inside you will see:
____________________________________________________________________________________
<<<<<< HEAD
your rahul2 code
=======
master code
>>>>>> master
____________________________________________________________________________________
2️⃣ Manually Edit

Decide:

Keep your code?

Keep master code?

Or combine both?
____________________________________________________________________________________
Delete:

<<<<<<
=======
>>>>>>>
____________________________________________________________________________________
Keep only final correct code.

Save file.

3️⃣ Tell Git Conflict is Fixed
git add abc
____________________________________________________________________________________
4️⃣ Finish Merge
git commit -m "fc"
____________________________________________________________________________________
Now conflict is resolved ✅

5️⃣ git push

